
@startuml

' Define classes and their relationships
class University {
}

class Department {
}

class ResearchGroup {
    - name: String
    - department: Department
}

class Researcher {
    - name: String
    - researchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class Project {
    - title: String
    - description: String
}

class WorkPackage {
    - title: String
    - description: String
    - leader: ResearchGroup
}

class Assignment {
    - startDate: Date
    - endDate: Date (optional)
}

' Relationships
University "1" -- "many" Department : contains
Department "1" -- "many" ResearchGroup : has
ResearchGroup "1" -- "many" Researcher : has
ResearchGroup "0..*" -- "1" WorkPackage : leads
Project "1" -- "many" WorkPackage : decomposes into
WorkPackage "1" -- "many" Assignment : has
Researcher "1" -- "many" Assignment : participates in
Assignment "1" -- "1" WorkPackage : assigned to
Assignment "1" -- "1" Researcher : performed by

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **University** contains **Departments**.
- **Departments** have **ResearchGroups**.
- **ResearchGroups**:
  - Have multiple **Researchers**.
  - Lead exactly one or more **WorkPackages**.
- **Projects** are decomposed into **WorkPackages**.
- A **WorkPackage** is led by a **ResearchGroup**.
- **Researchers** can be assigned to any **WorkPackage**, regardless of their group.
- An **Assignment** records when a **Researcher** works on a **WorkPackage**, including dates. This helps track service delivery across groups.

This model ensures traceability of inter-group collaboration and supports tracking when researchers move between groups or when leadership of WPs changes.